Russian Stocks: Surgut, TNK-BP, Mobile TeleSystems Are Active

-- B y   A l e x   N i c h o l s o n
-- 
2011-09-15T16:09:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-15/russian-stocks-surgut-lukoil-tnk-bp-mobile-telesystems-move.html
The 30-stock Micex Index climbed
for a third day, advancing 1.4 percent to 1,525.28 by the 6:45
p.m. close in Moscow. The dollar-denominated RTS Index rose 2.1
percent to 1,603.39 rubles.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO Mobile TeleSystems (MTSI RX), the country’s largest
mobile-phone operator, jumped as much as 3.3 percent before
closing up 1.3 percent at 205.06 rubles.  France Telecom SA (FTE) 
denied it was in stake-swap talks with the Russian company’s
controlling shareholder, AFK Sistema.  OAO Surgutneftegas (SNGS RX), an oil producer, climbed the
most in a month, adding 5 percent to 24.963 rubles. UniCredit
SpA lifted its recommendation for the shares to “buy” from
“hold,” citing the “positive impact” of government oil-tax
changes.  TNK-BP (TNBP RX), the Russian oil venture owned by BP Plc
and a group of billionaires, rose 1.5 percent to 81.75 rubles,
its strongest level in a week. The company pledged $45 billion
over the next decade to lift output 1 percent to 2 percent a
year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Nicholson in Moscow at 
